name: We've got all the Kubes!
body: Build `k8sattributesprocessor`, `headers_setter` and `k8seventsreceiver` in the Lumigo OpenTelemetry Collector, which we need in the upcoming [Lumigo Kubernetes Operator](https://github.com/lumigo-io/lumigo-kubernetes-operator/)!

name: Rebase on v0.60.0, tailor built-in capabilities with OCB
body:
Rebase on v0.60.0.

Use the [OpenTelemetry Collector Builder (OCB)](https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-collector/tree/main/cmd/builder) to compile all and only the following capabilities.

Receivers:
- otlp

Processors:
  - batchprocessor
  - redactionprocessor
  - resourceprocessor
  - transformprocessor

Exporters:
- awskinesisexporter
- loggingexporter

Extensions:
- lumigoauthextension
- healthcheckextension

name: LumigoAuth v1
body: Introduce an extension called `lumigoauth` that ensures that HTTP requests processed by the associated receivers come in with an `Authentication: LumigoToken <token>` header, and make the value of the token available in the `auth` context for later processing.
